<DOC><DOCNO> AP890111-0101 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-11-89 1234EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w PM-Reagan-Hostages     01-11 0143</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Reagan-Hostages,130</SECOND><HEAD>President Thinks of Hostages, Won't Guess When They'll be Freed</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan said today the plight ofAmerican hostages in Lebanon has never been out of his mind sincethey were seized, but he declined to speculate on whether they mightbe released as he leaves office.   ``I can only pray and continue what we've been (doing),'' Reagantold reporters in response to a question. ``We've been exploringevery channel possible for their release, and they've never been outof my mind since they were so unfairly seized.''   The president was then asked if there might be a repeat of whathappened in 1981, when American hostages held in Iran were releasedon Inauguration Day.   ``I won't hazard any speculation on that,'' he said. ``It's just,it's a great tragedy. We hope that it can be resolved.''</TEXT></DOC>